name: CJ Abrams
summary: The Washington Nationals have demoted All-Star shortstop CJ Abrams to Triple-A due to an unspecified "internal issue." The move comes after Abrams reportedly spent the night before a game at a casino until 8 AM. The Nationals have not officially confirmed that the demotion is related to the casino incident, but it is widely believed to be the reason. Abrams has been a bright spot for the Nationals this season, batting .322 with 5 home runs and 14 stolen bases in 46 games. His demotion is a significant blow to the team, who are currently in last place in the NL East.
